Here is a step-by-step guide to help you develop a C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file:

Step 1: Open the text file using the fstream library

You will need to use the fstream library to open the text file and read it line by line. You can use the following code snippet to open the text file:

```
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
   // Open the file
   fstream file;
   file.open("filename.txt");
   if(!file)
   {
      cout << "Error opening file";
      return 1;
   }
   // Read the file
   string line;
   int count = 0;
   while(getline(file, line))
   {
      // Search for the word
      size_t pos = line.find("specific word");
      while(pos != string::npos)
      {
         // Increment the counter
         count++;
         // Find the next occurrence of the word
         pos = line.find("specific word", pos+1);
      }
   }
   // Close the file
   file.close();
   return 0;
}
```

Step 2: Count the number of occurrences of the specific word

To count the number of occurrences of the specific word in the file, you will need to use the find() function of the string class. You can use the following code snippet to count the number of occurrences:

```
// Search for the word
size_t pos = line.find("specific word");
while(pos != string::npos)
{
   // Increment the counter
   count++;
   // Find the next occurrence of the word
   pos = line.find("specific word", pos+1);
}
```

Step 3: Print the result

After you have counted the number of occurrences of the specific word, you can print the result using the cout statement. You can use the following code snippet to print the result:

```
// Print the result
cout << "The word was found " << count << " times in the file";
```

Step 4: Close the file

Finally, you will need to close the file using the close() function of the fstream class. You can use the following code snippet to close the file:

```
// Close the file
file.close();
```

That's it! You now have a C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file.

